  "texts": [
    "In aging research, they were found to be particularly valuable due to their ability to analyze diverse longitudinal data types, such genomic sequencing, blood biomarker trends, and daily physical activity logs, allowing researchers to study and interpret patterns in the aging process [16,19].Within the broader category of DNNs, specific architectures have been developed to tackle different types of data and tasks.",
    "Among others, Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) identify patterns in grid-like data, such as images, by capturing spatial features across multiple layers [20].",
    "They are optimized for processing visual information and streamline image analysis.",
    "In contrast, Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) capture patterns in sequential data such as genomic sequences, speech, and real-time sensor data by using feedback loops that allow information to be retained across steps in a sequence.",
    "They incorporate information from previous inputs to influence future outputs, using a primitive form of memory [21]."
  ],
